          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Since I've had a lot of experience traveling at this point in my life, I decided to do a mini series about my travel favorites. This is the final of three posts in this series. See my first post on "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "http://www.everydayaccountsblog.com/2016/03/2016-favorites-travel-tech/",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "travel tech here"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", and my second post on "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "http://www.everydayaccountsblog.com/2016/04/2016-favorites-packing-gear/",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "packing gear here"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". Today I'm sharing my favorite clothing and products that I brought with me on "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "http://www.everydayaccountsblog.com/2015/12/hello-friends-a-big-announcement/",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "our big Europe trip"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Daniel and I didn't pack much to take with us on our trip. This made it all the more important (and difficult!) to pick out good quality clothing and products to bring. These are my very favorite clothing items and products that I brought with me in my backpack."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "em"
              }
            ],
            "text": "This post contains some Amazon affiliate links, meaning if you click on the link, I receive a small percentage of the sale, but the price doesn't change for you."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Clothing"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "strong"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Plaid Scarf"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/2016-04-08-13.31.54-1-1024x793.jpg",
              "alt": "2016-04-08 13.31.54",
              "title": null
            },
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "http://www.everydayaccountsblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/2016-04-08-13.31.54-1.jpg",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "I brought a couple of scarves with me just to change it up, but this navy and red plaid scarf is my favorite. It works as a scarf, a wrap, or a pillow for long train rides. :)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "strong"
              }
            ],
            "text": "ECCO Abelone Tall Boots (Brown)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Up until two days before our trip to Europe (Christmas Eve of last year), I had planned to wear a pair of boots I had purchased on clearance at a GAP outlet a year before. I thought they'd be fine, and I didn't want to spend money on shoes that would just wear out from all of the walking we planned to do. Well, the sole of those boots started to fall off on Christmas Eve! My husband actually still needed shoes too, so we both headed to the mall Christmas Eve afternoon. All I knew was I needed something that would be comfortable for walking thousands of steps every day, and it had to keep my feet warm for the European winter. As a bonus, I really wanted something that I could wear casually with jeans AND that I could wear with leggings and one dress I brought with me. Well, I found the perfect thing! The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "http://amzn.to/2jjQRE9",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "ECCO Abelone Tall Boots"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "...."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "[caption id=\"attachment_6229\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1024\"]"
          },
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/2016-04-08-13.33.11-1024x768.jpg",
              "alt": "2016-04-08 13.33.11",
              "title": null
            },
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "http://www.everydayaccountsblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/2016-04-08-13.33.11.jpg",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " My very well-loved boots[/caption]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Yes, these boots look pretty worn out, but I wore them every single day for nearly three months. They were the only shoes I brought with me so that I didn't have to make room for shoes in my backpack. They are amazing! ECCO is a brand that specializes in being comfortable while still being stylish. The soles of these shoes formed perfectly to my feet. I rarely had aching feet which is amazing because we walked anywhere from 15,000 to 35,000 steps almost every day. While real leather isn't made to go through all of the snow and rain that we experienced (resulting in the wear and tear pictured above), the quality did allow the boot to stay in good walking condition throughout the whole three months, and I don't think fake leather shoes would have lasted."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "strong"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Northface Women's Thermoball Hooded Parka (Black)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "[caption id=\"attachment_6233\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1024\"]"
          },
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/20160112_144059-1024x576.jpg",
              "alt": "20160112_144059",
              "title": null
            },
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "http://www.everydayaccountsblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/20160112_144059.jpg",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " Wearing my warm coat at "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "http://www.everydayaccountsblog.com/2016/02/travel-with-me-adventure-in-the-scottish-highlands/",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "Loch Ness"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "[/caption]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Other than my "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "http://www.everydayaccountsblog.com/2016/04/2016-favorites-packing-gear/",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "backpack"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and boots (above), I had one more larger purchase to make for a winter backpacking trip in Europe - a warm and lightweight coat. This "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "http://amzn.to/2jkXA0k",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "Northface Thermoball Hooded Parka"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "  in black was exactly what I needed. Its thermoball technology somehow makes the jacket very warm without being heavy at all. It is knee-length, has a hood, and has the weight of a light rain jacket. This combined with a warm scarf and gloves kept me very warm on even the coldest and rainiest days. While it is not waterproof, it did keep the water outside the jacket, and it dries very quickly. Today it still looks as good as new after being worn every day for three months. I will be wearing this jacket for years!"
          }
        ]
      },
